text: The interior tree frog (Dendropsophus melanargyreus) is a frog that lives in Bolivia, French Guiana, Paraguay, and Brazil. This frog is 35.0 mm long from nose to rear end, not counting the legs. This frog lives near the edges of forests and inside forests near water. People see it on leaves and branches. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Interior tree frog
